02:06:12.980 --> 02:06:19.340 position:56%
which are the questions and which
are the more probable investigations

02:06:19.340 --> 02:06:22.770
that can give some
answers to these questions.

02:06:22.770 --> 02:06:29.760
So I think that this is a good idea
and this is also probably the idea

02:06:29.760 --> 02:06:37.650
that we could keep in mind when
trying to build this linking

02:06:37.650 --> 02:06:45.860
between all the different databases
so you need different users.

02:06:45.860 --> 02:06:49.330
&gt;&gt; I think we might
need new librarians too,

02:06:49.330 --> 02:06:53.410
to help the art historian
going to the library

02:06:53.410 --> 02:06:58.430
to discover these tremendous assets
because so far as I can tell,

02:06:58.430 --> 02:07:04.020 position:56%
some of these are available already,
you just have to know where to look.

02:07:04.020 --> 02:07:06.160
But in terms of training,
I wasn't actually thinking

02:07:06.160 --> 02:07:09.090
of getting the conversation
on to training quite yet

02:07:09.090 --> 02:07:11.100
but if we can just stay
on that for a moment,

02:07:11.100 --> 02:07:14.440
Merv and Joe you both trained
as conservators so you had

02:07:14.440 --> 02:07:18.490
to have some science and I
think both of you actually came

02:07:18.490 --> 02:07:23.160
with science undergraduates rather
than art history as undergraduates

02:07:23.160 --> 02:07:26.780
and then picking up
science as a conservator,

02:07:26.780 --> 02:07:31.200
but if you can cast your minds
back, how difficult was it

02:07:31.200 --> 02:07:34.650
to have one class with some
people with a science background

02:07:34.650 --> 02:07:40.370
and some people with none
to have the same class?

02:07:40.370 --> 02:07:43.800
How do we need to solve
this problem?

02:07:43.800 --> 02:07:47.840
Who can be the trainers
for the art historians?

02:07:47.840 --> 02:07:53.580
&gt;&gt; I remember people
breaking out into tears trying

02:07:53.580 --> 02:07:56.210
to explain certain
aspects of science.

02:07:56.210 --> 02:07:58.890
I think the difficulty with
this type of training is

02:07:58.890 --> 02:08:03.540
that you don't necessarily
want to turn an art historian

02:08:03.540 --> 02:08:06.170
into a chemist or an
IT professional.

02:08:06.170 --> 02:08:09.560
You want to give the art
historian enough understanding

02:08:09.560 --> 02:08:12.320
to know the questions they
should be asking or to know

02:08:12.320 --> 02:08:15.490
who they should be
asking the questions of.

02:08:15.490 --> 02:08:18.290
I think for university students,

02:08:18.290 --> 02:08:21.080
we need to tell them you're an
art historian, you need to go

02:08:21.080 --> 02:08:25.330
to a chemistry class, insuring
that they understand the purpose

02:08:25.330 --> 02:08:27.920
of the chemistry class is to
allow them to ask questions rather

02:08:27.920 --> 02:08:31.090
than for them to become a
chemist is quite important.

02:08:31.090 --> 02:08:35.680
Having a clear understanding of
what people are trying to learn,

02:08:35.680 --> 02:08:38.790
so I would have thought for
an art historian the best way

02:08:38.790 --> 02:08:41.810
to get information together on
a particular artist would be

02:08:41.810 --> 02:08:45.220 position:56%
to get every single object ever
created by that artist into one room

02:08:45.220 --> 02:08:49.110
to gather together all of
the historical examinations

02:08:49.110 --> 02:08:52.090
that have been done of all of
those objects into the one room,

02:08:52.090 --> 02:08:54.630
and then all of the specialists
who did all of that work

02:08:54.630 --> 02:08:59.750
into the one room, all at your
beck and call and with a few people

02:08:59.750 --> 02:09:01.970
to interpret the different
languages that were done.

02:09:01.970 --> 02:09:06.050
Now theoretically, you could come
up with a computer model to do that

02:09:06.050 --> 02:09:09.990
but that's kind of where we're
aiming towards and I would say

02:09:09.990 --> 02:09:14.060
that a big issue here is
trust because if we're looking

02:09:14.060 --> 02:09:16.820
at pulling information from lots of
different places, you need to know

02:09:16.820 --> 02:09:19.180
