and that you can trust it.

02:09:19.180 --> 02:09:23.100 position:56%
We've got a lot of stuff in the main
press at the moment about fake news,

02:09:23.100 --> 02:09:27.440
which is slightly more severe
but people need to know

02:09:27.440 --> 02:09:29.910
if an examination has been
done, where was it done,

02:09:29.910 --> 02:09:33.610
do you feel that's an
okay interpretation

02:09:33.610 --> 02:09:36.460
because people aren't generally
going to be able to understand all

02:09:36.460 --> 02:09:39.430
of the raw data underneath
even if it's available.

02:09:39.430 --> 02:09:43.460
&gt;&gt; That was the case before it was
digital too wouldn't you agree?

02:09:43.460 --> 02:09:44.760
&gt;&gt; Yes.

02:09:44.760 --> 02:09:46.910
&gt;&gt; It's just that now with
the proliferation of access,

02:09:46.910 --> 02:09:48.210
we have to be more careful.

02:09:48.210 --> 02:09:49.510
&gt;&gt; You just have more
questions, that's the difficulty.

02:09:49.510 --> 02:09:53.660
I mean, instead of sort of spending
20 years exploring an archive,

02:09:53.660 --> 02:09:57.600
you may spend a week exploring
four so you're going to be hit

02:09:57.600 --> 02:10:00.050
